BACKGROUND: Patients with previously irradiated metastatic epidural spinal cord 
compression (MESCC) who are not surgical candidates are at high risk of 
neurologic deterioration due to disease in the setting of limited treatment 
options. We seek to establish the feasibility of using salvage spine 
stereotactic radiosurgery (SSRS) allowing for spinal cord dose constraint 
